<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile, traditional securities fraud has be=
en around for a long time, long enough that lawmakers decided it didn=E2=80=
=99t make sense for companies to get sued for every minor mistake they make=
 about their financial results or prospects, and so there are limits on wha=
t counts as traditional securities fraud. US securities law explicitly allo=
ws companies to be wrong about their earnings forecasts: There=C2=A0is a <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34349750.258392/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZWR1L3VzY29kZS90ZXh0LzE1Lzc4dS01/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB8a1a85ef" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> =E2=80=9Csafe harbor=E2=80=9D for =E2=80=9Cf=
orward-looking statements,=E2=80=9D</a>=C2=A0so if you predict that your Eb=
itda margin will expand by 500 basis points in 2024, but it actually expand=
s by only 50 basis points, your shareholders can=E2=80=99t sue you.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is an exception if you had =E2=80=9Cactu=
al knowledge=E2=80=9D that the statement is false.=C2=A0Did Lyft? On the on=
e hand, presumably the executives who approved this earnings release knew t=
hat they don=E2=80=99t expect margins to expand by 500 basis points. On the=
 other hand, presumably they didn=E2=80=99t notice the typo. I think they=
=E2=80=99re fine.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, though, they did the right thing here!=
=C2=A0They put the press release out after the market closed, and they corr=
ected it quickly and publicly before the market opened again.=C2=A0That=E2=
=80=99s kind of best practices for a public company, and also the best they=
 can do. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34349750.=
258392/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDItMTMv=
bHlmdC1vdXRsb29rLWJlYXRzLWVzdGltYXRlcy1hcy1tb3JlLXJpZGVycy1yZXR1cm4tc2hhcmV=
zLXN1cmdlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMTQyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3=
NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDIxNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZ=
g/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6c9faf52" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Bloomberg News reports</a>:<=
/p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CLyft clearly did one thin=
g right =E2=80=93 it corrected the error quickly and decisively,=E2=80=9D s=
aid Brad Foster, a partner specializing in securities litigation at corpora=
te law firm Haynes Boone. =E2=80=9CThe reality is that people make mistakes=
, and mistakes are not securities fraud.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well, sometimes they are, but not like this. L=
yft can=E2=80=99t stop its shareholders from trading after hours, but in so=
me rough sense that=E2=80=99s not its=C2=A0responsibility. If you want to t=
rade in the after-hours market the second the press release hits the tape,=
=C2=A0the risk of typos is on you.</p>
